One of the more regular sights in South African sport is youngsters sticking up their hands in various sporting codes and tournaments. However, in this year’s Ram Slam T20 challenge, it’s been rather difficult to find them as the older guard has generally lit up the tournament. At least we’ve been able to find five young guns that have impressed – even though we had to bump up the maximum age to 25!  SIBONELO MAKHANYA (Dolphins)  THEUNIS DE BRUYN (Knights)  KAGISO RABADA (Highveld Lions)  WIAAN MULDER (Highveld Lions)  AIDEN MARKRAM (Titans)  Read original story on citizen.co.za